{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"84c147e9-2e0c-4a16-8be1-2d7e2948b6d5","content":"\n\nHere's the mapping and new command:\n\n| VSTest flag | Microsoft.Testing.Platform | NuGet package needed |\n|---|---|---|\n| `--logger trx` | `--report-trx` | `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` | `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` | `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `--crashdump` | `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump` |\n| `--blame-hang` | `--hangdump` | `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump` |\n| `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` | `--hangdump-timeout 5m` | *(same package)* |\n\n**New command:**\n\n```bash\ndotnet test -- \\\n  --filter \"Category=Integration\" \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\nThe `--` separator forwards everything to the test platform. You also need these in your test `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n<OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0a822c2f-8282-4f10-9ebe-a700258e3dff","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their CI test command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MSTest runner) on .NET 8. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing infrastructure, not a code change request.\n\nLet me provide the equivalent command for Microsoft.Testing.Platform.\n\nKey differences:\n- `--filter` → `--filter` (same)\n- `--logger trx` → `--report-trx` \n- `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` → `--collect-coverage` with `--coverage-output-format cobertura` (or using Microsoft.CodeCoverage package)\n- `--blame-crash` → `--crashdump`\n\n\n- `--blame-hang` → `--hangdump`\n- `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` → `--hangdump-timeout 5m`\n\nWhen using `dotnet test` with Microsoft.Testing.Platform, the command structure shifts slightly—the filter syntax remains the same, but TRX reporting requires the Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport package and uses `--report-trx`, while code coverage integration through Microsoft.CodeCoverage handles the cobertura format output.\n\nBuilding the command with crash dumps, hang dumps, and coverage collection...\n\nFor .NET 8 specifically, I need to consider whether `dotnet test` uses the VSTest compatibility layer by default or if there's a way to invoke Microsoft.Testing.Platform directly. It looks like adding `<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>` to the project file might enable native support, but I should verify the exact configuration needed. I'm clarifying the setup requirements for .NET 8 with Microsoft.Testing.Platform—specifically that you need to enable `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` in the project file for `dotnet test` integration, and then pass the platform-specific arguments after the `--` separator in the command.","outputTokens":1587},"id":"22a0982c-6e61-44dd-997d-8aa1e9f227e2","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:45:18.544Z","parentId":"091441da-3cbe-43f1-a389-a4c03325c5d1"}
